-- Est Media Declines for Third Day After Auction of Shares Fails
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-23T09:13:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/est-media-declines-for-third-day-after-auction-of-shares-fails.html
 Est Media Vagyonkezelo Nyrt., a
Hungarian entertainment company, declined for a third day after
an auction of its shares failed.  The shares dropped as much as 11 percent to 86 forint and
traded 6.2 percent lower by 10:47 a.m. in Budapest at 91 forint,
1 forint more than its lowest ever closing price on April 11.  No bids were accepted at the auction on the Budapest Stock
Exchange on April 20, broker Equilor Befektetesi Zrt., which
conducted the sale, said in a statement sent by e-mail. The
company offered 2.7 million shares at the auction.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
